{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-index-js","path":"/2018/10/getty-images-homepage/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"ff58ffae-eb78-5a7a-9cac-454051acddfe","html":"<p>The website for Getty Images is currently undergoing a complete redesign. The company is rolling the build out in phases, so only a few pages have been redeveloped so far. It has been a lot of work, but everything is bringing the brand in the right direction.</p>\n<hr/>\n<h2>The Homepage</h2>\n<p>I really wanted to learn and use something new for the homepage and the design gave me the perfect opportunity to use CSS grid. I worked closely with Leina Leung during prototyping and we came up with a grid that worked across all browser sizes. CSS grid is still not supported by all browsers, so a fallback was written that changes the layout to a grid made of float elements. The only main difference between the protype and production code is <code>@supports</code> was ditched in favor of using a media query specific to IE.</p>\n<h3>Prototype</h3>\n<div class=\"flex-vid\">\n  <iframe height=\"575\" scrolling=\"no\" title=\"CSS Grid for Getty Images\" src=\"//codepen.io/thomasvaeth/embed/mjLLKO/?height=575&theme-id=0&default-tab=css,result\" frameborder=\"no\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"width: 100%;\"></iframe>\n</div>\n<p>The demo is best viewed with the SCSS tab closed and the zoom set to 0.5x or 0.25x.</p>\n<h3>Production</h3>\n<div class=\"browser\">\n  <span class=\"browser__dots\"></span>\n  <figure class=\"browser__img\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1200px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 54.833333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Getty Images Website\" title=\"Getty Images Website\" src=\"/static/9042556f2808a88355cca9fb1ba42d3c/e5166/getty-images-homepage-1.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/9042556f2808a88355cca9fb1ba42d3c/70ebb/getty-images-homepage-1.jpg 350w,\n/static/9042556f2808a88355cca9fb1ba42d3c/29d31/getty-images-homepage-1.jpg 700w,\n/static/9042556f2808a88355cca9fb1ba42d3c/e5166/getty-images-homepage-1.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  </figure>\n</div>\n<hr/>\n<h2>The Editorial Page</h2>\n<p>I also got to build the page for editorial images. The page uses a responsive masonry grid to show events in one to five columns depending on the browser size. The individual articles have a linear gradient overlay to make the titles easily readable and an opacity overlay that transitions on hover.</p>\n<div class=\"browser\">\n  <span class=\"browser__dots\"></span>\n  <figure class=\"browser__img\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1200px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 54.833333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Getty Images Website\" title=\"Getty Images Website\" src=\"/static/6b97e9b7204e0a4c48de0431084d9324/e5166/getty-images-homepage-2.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/6b97e9b7204e0a4c48de0431084d9324/70ebb/getty-images-homepage-2.jpg 350w,\n/static/6b97e9b7204e0a4c48de0431084d9324/29d31/getty-images-homepage-2.jpg 700w,\n/static/6b97e9b7204e0a4c48de0431084d9324/e5166/getty-images-homepage-2.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  </figure>\n</div>\n<hr/>\n<div class=\"browser\">\n  <span class=\"browser__dots\"></span>\n  <figure class=\"browser__img\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1200px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 438.99999999999994%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"Getty Images Website\" title=\"Getty Images Website\" src=\"/static/f0e444c8fde96acbf684001ae49feac2/e5166/getty-images-homepage-3.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/f0e444c8fde96acbf684001ae49feac2/70ebb/getty-images-homepage-3.jpg 350w,\n/static/f0e444c8fde96acbf684001ae49feac2/29d31/getty-images-homepage-3.jpg 700w,\n/static/f0e444c8fde96acbf684001ae49feac2/e5166/getty-images-homepage-3.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  </figure>\n</div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Getty Images Homepage","description":"","date":"October 2018","image":{"id":"846d794a-51bf-529d-a407-c8c27455a557","publicURL":"/static/getty-images-homepage-620af37193c43eb814c91143490366b5.jpg"}},"fields":{"slug":"/2018/10/getty-images-homepage/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2018/10/getty-images-homepage/"}}}